git --version

git init ---> For creating the local empty repository
 
git config --global user.name <username>

git config --global user.email <email of github repo>

git config --list  ---> will diplay the list of users

git status --> will displa the status of branch
   * --> indicates where we are

git clone <remote url> ---> clone remote repo to your local

git add . --> moving files to stagging area

git commit -m "commit message" --> commiting the files to local repo

git remote add <aliasname> <remoteurl> add the remote repo to local

git remote ---> will show the remote list

git branch --> will display the branches in local

git branch <branchname> --> for creating new branch

git checkout <branch name> --> will take u into that branch

git push origin master  --> for pushing local repo to remote repo

git pull origin master  ---> updating the working directory 

git fetch + git merge = git pull

git fetch --> will fetch the files from remote repo to local repo

git merge origin/master --> will be updated the ur working directory 

git diff HEAD --> will diplay the changes in the last commit

git rebase --> also used for integrating the branches but rebase will give linear commits of all

git stash ---> you are working on some project ...u not yet committed changes but you want to switch other branch with out commiting the present wotking branch... for that just stash
               your working copy and can move to 
to push new stash into your stack. git stash

git stash list ---> will give the stashes you have stored

git stash aplly --> will aplly the most recent satsh
 
git stash drop --> will remove the satsh

git stash pop --> will apply and then remove

git reset <filename> will move the files from staging are to working directory

git revert HEAD --> will revert the last commit from local

git tag -a <tag name>

 --- For remove or delete ---

git remote rm <remote alias name>

git branch -d <branch name>

git tag -d <tag name>



